%F A001542 a(n) = 2*A001109(n).
%F A001542 a(n) = ((3+2*sqrt(2))^n - (3-2*sqrt(2))^n) / (2*sqrt(2)).
%F A001542 G.f.: 2*x/(1-6*x+x^2).
%F A001542 a(n) = sqrt(2*(A001541(n))^2 - 2)/2. - _Barry E. Williams_, May 07 2000
%F A001542 a(n) = (C^(2n) - C^(-2n))/sqrt(8) where C = sqrt(2) + 1. - _Gary W. Adamson_, May 11 2003
%F A001542 For all terms x of the sequence, 2*x^2 + 1 is a square. Limit_{n->oo} a(n)/a(n-1) = 3 + 2*sqrt(2). - _Gregory V. Richardson_, Oct 10 2002
%F A001542 For n > 0: a(n) = A001652(n) + A046090(n) - A001653(n); e.g., 70 = 119 + 120 - 169. Also a(n) = A001652(n - 1) + A046090(n - 1) + A001653(n - 1); e.g., 70 = 20 + 21 + 29. Also a(n)^2 + 1 = A001653(n - 1)*A001653(n); e.g., 12^2 + 1 = 145 = 5*29. Also a(n + 1)^2 = A084703(n + 1) = A001652(n)*A001652(n + 1) + A046090(n)*A046090(n + 1). - _Charlie Marion_, Jul 01 2003
%F A001542 a(n) = ((1+sqrt(2))^(2*n) - (1-sqrt(2))^(2*n))/(2*sqrt(2)). - _Antonio Alberto Olivares_, Dec 24 2003
%F A001542 2*A001541(k)*A001653(n)*A001653(n+k) = A001653(n)^2 + A001653(n+k)^2 + a(k)^2; e.g., 2*3*5*29 = 5^2 + 29^2 + 2^2; 2*99*29*5741 = 29^2 + 5741^2 + 70^2. - _Charlie Marion_, Oct 12 2007
%F A001542 a(n) = sinh(2*n*arcsinh(1))/sqrt(2). - _Herbert Kociemba_, Apr 24 2008
%F A001542 For n > 0, a(n) = A001653(n) + A002315(n-1). - _Richard R. Forberg_, Aug 31 2013
%F A001542 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 2*A001541(n-1); e.g., a(4) = 70 = 3*12 + 2*17. - _Zak Seidov_, Dec 19 2013
%F A001542 a(n)^2 + 1^2 = A115598(n)^2 + (A115598(n)+1)^2. - _Hermann Stamm-Wilbrandt_, Jul 27 2014
%F A001542 Sum _{n >= 1} 1/( a(n) + 1/a(n) ) = 1/2. - _Peter Bala_, Mar 25 2015
%F A001542 E.g.f.: exp(3*x)*sinh(2*sqrt(2)*x)/sqrt(2). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Dec 07 2016
%F A001542 A007814(a(n)) = A001511(n). See Mathematical Reflections link. - _Michel Marcus_, Jan 06 2017
%F A001542 a(n) = -a(-n) for all n in Z. - _Michael Somos_, Jan 20 2017
%F A001542 From _A.H.M. Smeets_, May 28 2017: (Start)
%F A001542 A051009(n) = a(2^(n-2)).
%F A001542 a(2n) = 2*a(2)*A001541(n).
%F A001542 A001541(n)/a(n) > sqrt(2) > 2*a(n)/A001541(n). (End)
%F A001542 a(A298210(n)) = A002349(2*n^2). - _A.H.M. Smeets_, Jan 25 2018
%F A001542 a(n) = A000129(n)*A002203(n). - _Adam Mohamed_, Jul 20 2024
